    "plan_content": "Here is the complete implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n**4 new files + 1 edit**, all following the exact patterns of the existing `next/server` / `userAgent` module.\n\n### Files to create\n\n**1. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`** — Core implementation (self-contained, no external deps)\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 entries: AU, BR, CA, CN, DE, FR, GB, IN, JP, US)\n- `Geo` interface with 7 optional `string` fields\n- `geoFromHeaders(headers: Headers): Geo` — reads Vercel headers first, falls back to `cf-ipcountry` for countryCode; derives `country` from the map; `headers.get() ?? undefined` normalises `null → undefined`\n- `geo({ headers }): Geo` — thin wrapper (mirrors `userAgent`)\n- `isInRegion(geo, regions)` — `toUpperCase()` on both sides for case-insensitive match\n- `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2)` — Haversine formula, R = 6371 km\n\n**2. `packages/next/geo.js`** — CJS public entry point (mirrors `server.js`)\n- Same dual-export pattern: `module.exports = geoExports` + explicit `exports.xxx` assignments\n- `require('next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo')` for each export\n\n**3. `packages/next/geo.d.ts`** — TypeScript declarations (mirrors `server.d.ts`)\n- `export type { Geo }` + `export { geo, geoFromHeaders, isInRegion, geoDistance }` all from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo`\n\n**4. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`** — Jest test suite (co-located, same pattern as `adapters/headers.test.ts`; no extra test-framework imports needed since Jest globals are project-wide)\n- Tests: Vercel headers extraction, missing headers → `undefined`, Cloudflare fallback, Vercel-over-CF priority, all 10 country code lookups, unknown code → `undefined`, `isInRegion` (match / miss / case-insensitive / undefined), `geoDistance` NY→London ≈5570 km ±50, identical coords → 0\n\n### File to edit\n\n**5. `packages/next/package.json`** — Insert after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetical: g follows f):\n```diff\n     \"form.js\",\n     \"form.d.ts\",\n+    \"geo.js\",\n+    \"geo.d.ts\",\n     \"router.js\",\n```\n\n### Verification\n1. `pnpm --filter=next types` — zero TS errors\n2. `pnpm test-unit` — all geo tests pass\n3. `pnpm --filter=next build` + `node -e \"const {geo}=require('./packages/next/geo.js');console.log(geo)\"` — function printed, not undefined",
